<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Musicians</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/scss" href="musicianspitch.scss">

  </head>

  <body class="musicians-sell">
    <script>

    $(function(){
    $('.carousel').carousel();
});
    </script>

    <div class='sellingline'>
      <h1>Why choose PlayMyParty?</h1>
      <p>
        PlayMyParty helps show case a Musicians musical talent with just a click of a button.
      </p>
    </div>



    <div class='container_images'>
      <div class='image'>
        <%= image_tag "dj1.jpg"%>
      </div>
      <div class='overlay'>
        <div class='text'>
          <p>DVBBS Veld, August 2016 </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='container_images'>
      <div class='image'>
        <%= image_tag "band1.jpg"%>
      </div>
      <div class='overlay'>
        <div class='text'>
          <p>United Molsen Amphitheatre, June 2015</p>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='container_images'>
      <div class='image'>
        <%= image_tag "dj2.jpg" %>
      </div>
      <div class='overlay'>
        <div class='text'>
          <p>Shawn Frank Coda, March 2017</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='p2'>
    <h3>
    How will PlayMyParty help my career?
    </h3>
    <p>
    As a Musician, you simply create an account that displays your musical talent. You choose the type of genre you play, the distance you are willing to travel and your hourly rate.
    Your profile will now be shown in our Musician database.
    Currently our Musicians on average get 4-5 invites a day to play an Event.
    A majority of our Musicans choose to play 1-3 events per week.
    </p>
    </div>

    <div class='titles'>
    <h2>
    Play the show you want to play. You are in control of future events!
    </h2>
    <h3>
    Welcome to the PlayMyParty family.
    </h3>
    </div>
    <div id="carouselExampleIndicators" class="carousel slide slideposition" data-ride="carousel">
      <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="2"></li>
      </ol>

      <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="item active">
          <img class="d-block w-100" src="/assets/Jazzartist.jpg" alt="First slide">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
            <h5>User: JazzyTwo</h5>
            <p>I've been getting many notification bookings popping up "Come play at my Jazz event", It’s funny too because realistically I don’t actively promote my Jazz band. With Play My Party I get 4-5 invites per day, I can't imagine my life without Play My Party.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="item">
          <img class="d-block w-100" src="/assets/dj3.jpg" alt="Second slide">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
            <h5>User: Thriller</h5>
          <p>"I'm a new Dj getting into the scene. I didn't know how to get my name out there but with Play My Party I now get bookings from bars all over the GTA."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

        <div class="item ">
          <img class="d-block w-100" src="/assets/kpop3.jpg" alt="Third slide">
          <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
            <h5>User: IU</h5>
            <p>"We are a Korean pop group trying to break out into the Toronto music scene. Before Play My Party we would get maybe 1-2 events per month, since we started using Play My Party we get 3-5 Korean Pop shows per month. We also love that their is no membership fee. Play My Party was very easy to navigate through." </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

      <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carouselExampleIndicators" role="button" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
      </a>
      <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carouselExampleIndicators" role="button" data-slide="next">
        <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </body>

</html>
